    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending) is accepted at Medium assurance level. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall — Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) — is acknowledged and accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 static compression-bending is the predicate-consistent regulatory test method, model influence is rated Medium, and the quantitative comparison metrics (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) are satisfied across all three QoIs and all three independent modeling teams. The overall body of evidence supports a determination that the FEA modeling framework is sufficiently credible for its intended regulatory use.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
